President Joe Biden has declared a state of emergency for the Mashpee Wampanoag Tribe due to the effects of Tropical Storm Henri. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to the Tribe. FEMA is authorized to allocate resources and equipment to help mitigate the impact of the emergency. The assistance will be funded at 75 percent federal funding and will include mass care, evacuation, and shelter support. James R. McPherson has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA news desk.